# git-lfs: store audio blobs outside regular git, so clones stay fast and
# the 100 MB per-file push limit on GitHub doesn't reject large MP3s
# (e.g. dubfire-sake-audio.mp3 at 122 MB).
#
# Pointer files are tiny (~130 bytes) and live in regular git; the actual
# bytes live on GitHub's LFS servers. Free tier: 1 GB storage / 1 GB
# bandwidth per month — covers ~6 full-length tracks.
projects/**/*.mp3 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
projects/**/*.wav filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mp3             filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.wav             filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
